<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The species was erected in genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhang, Zhong &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Margituberculatus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Margituberculatus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Margituberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on only one alate viviparous female (
<bibRefCitation author="Zhang, GX" journalOrPublisher="Vol. 1. Science Press, Beijing" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="360 - 403" refId="B20" refString="Zhang, GX, Zhong, TS, Zhang, WY, 1992. Homoptera: Aphidoidea. In: The Comprehensive Scientific Expedition to the Qinghai-Xizang Plateau, Insects of the Hengduan Mountains Regions. Vol. 1. Science Press, Beijing: 360 - 403" title="Homoptera: Aphidoidea." volumeTitle="The Comprehensive Scientific Expedition to the Qinghai-Xizang Plateau, Insects of the Hengduan Mountains Regions." year="1992">Zhang et al. 1992</bibRefCitation>
). Then the species was removed to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verma" authorityYear="1967" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aspidophorodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidophorodon" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aspidophorodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zhang, Zhong &amp; Zhang" baseAuthorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aspidophorodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidophorodon longituberculatum" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longituberculatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aspidophorodon longituberculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to the characters of processes and siphunculi; meanwhile, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aspidophorodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidophorodon cornuatum" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aspidophorodon cornuatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described as a new species (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4028.4.6" author="Chen, J" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="551 - 576" refId="B6" refString="Chen, J, Zhang, B, Zhu, XC, Jiang, LY, Qiao, GX, 2015. Review of the aphid genus Aspidophorodon Verma, 1967 with descriptions of three new species from China (Hemiptera: Aphididae: Aphidinae). Zootaxa 4028 (4): 551 - 576, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4028.4.6" title="Review of the aphid genus Aspidophorodon Verma, 1967 with descriptions of three new species from China (Hemiptera: Aphididae: Aphidinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4028.4.6" volume="4028" year="2015">Chen et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
). At that time, there were no alate viviparous females of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aspidophorodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidophorodon cornuatum" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aspidophorodon cornuatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, so it was difficult to compare with the two species. After several surveys in southwest China, apterous viviparous female (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Aspidophorodon (Eoessigia) longituberculatum (Zhang, Zhong &amp; Zhang, 1992). Alate viviparous female A dorsal view of body B dorsal view of abdomen. Apterous viviparous female C dorsal view of Aspidophorodon cornutus Qiao, 2015 syn. nov. Alate viviparous female D dorsal view of Aspidophorodon cornutum Qiao, 2015 syn. nov. E dorsal view of abdomen of Aspidophorodon cornutum Qiao, 2015 syn. nov. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702353" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">18C</figureCitation>
) and alate viviparous female (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Aspidophorodon (Eoessigia) longituberculatum (Zhang, Zhong &amp; Zhang, 1992). Alate viviparous female A dorsal view of body B dorsal view of abdomen. Apterous viviparous female C dorsal view of Aspidophorodon cornutus Qiao, 2015 syn. nov. Alate viviparous female D dorsal view of Aspidophorodon cornutum Qiao, 2015 syn. nov. E dorsal view of abdomen of Aspidophorodon cornutum Qiao, 2015 syn. nov. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702353" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">18D</figureCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aspidophorodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidophorodon cornuatum" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aspidophorodon cornuatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected. The alate viviparous female of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aspidophorodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidophorodon cornuatum" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aspidophorodon cornuatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is with marginal processes on abdominal tergites I-IV (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Aspidophorodon (Eoessigia) longituberculatum (Zhang, Zhong &amp; Zhang, 1992). Alate viviparous female A dorsal view of body B dorsal view of abdomen. Apterous viviparous female C dorsal view of Aspidophorodon cornutus Qiao, 2015 syn. nov. Alate viviparous female D dorsal view of Aspidophorodon cornutum Qiao, 2015 syn. nov. E dorsal view of abdomen of Aspidophorodon cornutum Qiao, 2015 syn. nov. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702353" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">18E</figureCitation>
) which is the same as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zhang, Zhong &amp; Zhang" baseAuthorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aspidophorodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidophorodon longituberculatum" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longituberculatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aspidophorodon longituberculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Aspidophorodon (Eoessigia) longituberculatum (Zhang, Zhong &amp; Zhang, 1992). Alate viviparous female A dorsal view of body B dorsal view of abdomen. Apterous viviparous female C dorsal view of Aspidophorodon cornutus Qiao, 2015 syn. nov. Alate viviparous female D dorsal view of Aspidophorodon cornutum Qiao, 2015 syn. nov. E dorsal view of abdomen of Aspidophorodon cornutum Qiao, 2015 syn. nov. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702353" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">18A, B</figureCitation>
). The molecular data of alate viviparous females of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zhang, Zhong &amp; Zhang" baseAuthorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aspidophorodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidophorodon longituberculatum" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longituberculatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aspidophorodon longituberculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and apterous viviparous females of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aspidophorodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidophorodon cornuatum" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aspidophorodon cornuatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
support they are the same species (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Neighbour-joining tree for Aspidophorodon samples based on COI sequences." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702358" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">23</figureCitation>
). So, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aspidophorodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidophorodon cornuatum" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cornuatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aspidophorodon cornuatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Qiao, 2015 should be considered as junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zhang, Zhong &amp; Zhang" baseAuthorityYear="1992" class="Insecta" family="Aphididae" genus="Aspidophorodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aspidophorodon longituberculatum" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longituberculatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aspidophorodon longituberculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Zhang, Zhong &amp; Zhang, 1992).
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702353" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 18" startId="F18">
